Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The path to check.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success - The operation succeeded.
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.478af95a-2d89-46b9-80a4-32e4c8f19e5c.prompt=Enter a value for password 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.49b29be1-ecc6-4692-88ed-712ed8aae235.prompt=Enter a value for password 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.4ba41a3c-4816-4d44-95b5-076dda6281e5.transition.description=The scriptlet executed successfully. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.4f4cdd38-18b9-4663-8930-2a804d32d4c0.transition.description=The VB script was run on the remote machine. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.53c25396-22c6-4298-81be-6a75b9accd37.transition.description=The UNC path for the remote location was computed. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.53d9745e-78a8-402e-9f88-c6b0ac0386f3.prompt=Enter a value for user 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.582971d7-a574-4386-aa11-15e82f1617a9.prompt=Host to run the script against\: 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.626ec444-d5ab-40d0-b584-b9e4cb298a31.description=
Converts a path and host into a unc path.

Inputs\:
host - the host you want to access the path on, For example\: laptop.
path - The path to access on host, For example\: c\:\temp.

Results\:
uncPath - The unc path to the specified path on the given host, its existence is not checked. So with the above inputs this would be\: \\laptop\c$\temp

Responses\:
success - unc path assembled successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.64d714bf-8111-4496-b63a-77b011d6bbd1.description=
Checks to see if a path is an existing file or folder.

Inputs\:
source - The full path path to check. This can be either a local path such as c\:\test.txt, or a unc path such as \\testhost\test.txt. This path is relative to the Windows RAS host that the operation is running on.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for username.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not exist.
success - The operation succeeded.
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.6f9c9e9f-d8bb-408e-bc29-2ff4482324e5.transition.description=The vbscript had errors and couldn't be executed successfully.The error returned when trying to run the script was\: ${scriptError}. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.70c2c6f3-0520-461b-a02a-a99c49a94b6c.transition.description=The file with the VB script was removed from the remote machine. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.7487759e-77de-449d-91ed-cb8cc6c32e90.transition.description=The file with the VB script couldn't be removed from the remote machine. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.788e34a6-c0c0-4b1f-a2de-7c65b26bb9f5.prompt=Alternate Credentials - Password\: 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.7abc96ad-3a52-4ad6-b7b8-7c6a984e139d.description=
Generates a random number.

Inputs\:
max - The maximum number that can be returned.
min - The minimum number that can be returned.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed Successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
A random number between max and min (inclusive)
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.8eee1093-9e0d-4eed-af9b-10b2a4999a92.transition.description=A random number couldn't be generated for renaming the remote file. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.8f6047d0-fadf-4e2e-a11d-825531ed84c0.transition.description=The remote script file couldn't be renamed. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.9949ec29-07a3-40a9-be6b-7a4397c8eba5.prompt=Password for remote user\: 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.9fa1a936-3d60-4c7b-85cc-dd463a0e9d5f.transition.description=The remote script file was renamed successfully. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.a0255b9d-8458-46b8-a781-306d1179663e.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null. Inputs\: keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable. Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value. notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.aa88488a-66b6-40ce-9d67-a0cab593c97b.transition.description=The VB script could not be run on the remote machine. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.ab5985ff-8e6f-4003-b310-11a012f537d3.transition.description=The VB script file couldn't be copied to the remote machine. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.ad7a94e7-11a6-4faf-aa80-720800fd0726.description=
Uses WMI to attempt to create a remote process on a machine.  The command passed should be formatted as though it was run on the command line.

CAUTION\: internally 'cmd /c' gets prepended to the command passed.  Also '2>tempfile 1>tempfile' get appended to the command so that we can attempt to capture stdout and stderr.
So your command will look like this when executed\:
	'cmd /c [yourcommand] 2>temperr 1>tempout'

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address of the target machine
command - the command you want executed
user - alternate credentials username
password - alternate credentials password
outputPath - network accessible path used by the operation to store temporary files. If not specified it points to \\host\admin$\temp\'. If this     path is not accessible you should change it to use another share that the host local system account has write access to. By default, the path will have to be  changed on Windows 2000 systems
currentDirectory - current directory
characterSet - The character encoding used by the operation (for instance, windows-1252). The default is UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - remote process successfully launched and has completed executing
failure - unable to start remote process

Extra Results\:
ReturnValue - return value from WMI for starting the process (not the exit value of the process)
ProcessID - the process id of the remote process
ProcessReturnCode - the return code of the remote process
StdOut - standard output from the remote process
StdErr - standard error from the remote process
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.ae3ab875-a4b9-4e6e-998e-7ba34d7423d5.transition.description=The VB script file was copied to the remote machine. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.b2a3178f-5998-4f19-a162-682e8bc7b433.prompt=Destination\: 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.be29dbcf-b23e-4b7a-b1c3-8f3e29e2c09d.description=
Deletes the file or directory specified.

Input Parameters\:
source - full path to file/directory to be removed (can be a UNC path)
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host while deleting.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
success - The specified path was successfuly removed.
failure - Unable to remove file/directory.
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.c0834246-d3d3-4517-abc3-9af278eb29e1.prompt=Enter a value for user 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.c1bb2cda-e86e-4229-988a-93f7bd253097.prompt=Enter a value for newName 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.c5abe226-a217-4f61-a151-2cebad6ee9af.transition.description=The VB script file doesn't exist on the RAS machine. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.c7d39c10-701a-4299-b61a-33f1cf984006.prompt=HostName\: 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.dbb5db71-9fdc-4168-a9de-fc1334860cb0.description=
Copies a file or directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The file or directory to copy.
destination - the location to copy the file or directory to.
removeSource - Specifies whether the source should be removed if the copy operation is successful (true, false).
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host during this operation.
password - The password for the user.
overwrite - If false the operation will fail if Destination exists.

Responses\:
success - Was able to copy file/directory.
failure - Unable to copy file/directory.

Note\:
This copy operation is modeled after the Windows command-line copy operation.  So given a sample directory structure\:
--DirectoryA
   |--File1
   |--File2
   |--DirectoryC
       |-File5

--DirectoryB
   |--File3
   |--File4

If your Source is "DirectoryA" and your Destination is "DirectoryB" your end result will be\:
--DirectoryA
   |--File1
   |--File2
   |--DirectoryC
       |-File5

--DirectoryB
   |--File3
   |--File4
   |--File1
   |--File2
   |--DirectoryC
       |-File5
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.description=This flow copies a vbscript file from the RAS machine to a given location from a remote machine, executes the script against the remote machine and deletes the remote file once completed. The RAS and the remote hosts need to be Windows machines. 
Inputs\:
scriptLocation - The full path to the vbscript file.This should not include the host name/IP . (Ex\: c\:\test\samplescript.vbs). 
remoteHost - The host to run the script against.
remoteHostUsername - The username for connecting to the remote host.
remoteHostPassword - The password for connecting to the remote host.
remoteLocation - The full path on the remote machine where the script is to be copied and from where it will be run. This should not contain the name of the host. (Ex\: c\:\test\). If this directory doesn't exist, the flow fails.

Responses\:
success - The vbscript file was copied and run remotely, being deleted afterwards.
failure - Something went wrong.
12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.e5c21066-a95e-41af-b226-b5cb5c0d2664.transition.description=The UNC path for the remote location can not be computed. 12bc011d-8c2a-404f-b34a-e5c98c8b14da.e8b7243d-88e1-4592-9183-0c37a88c27ec.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:

myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:

Scriptlet Example\:

FSRename changes the name of a file.  This operation will not move a file to a different directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The file to rename, including directory.
newName - The new name of the file, NOT INCLUDING DIRECTORY.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host for this operation.
password - Password for the user.
overwrite - If false the operation will fail if newName exists (true, false).

Responses\:
failure - The rename failed.
success - The rename succeeded.
